# Session Handoff Protocol

Reading 50 lines of a HANDOFF file costs ~150 tokens. Reconstructing lost context from scratch costs ~8,000 tokens. Write the HANDOFF.

## Starting a session
1. Read `docs/HANDOFF-<latest-date>.md` BEFORE opening any code file
2. Anchor immediately: "Per the HANDOFF, picking up from [X]. Today's task: [Y]."
3. Open ONLY files mentioned in the handoff — nothing else speculatively

## Ending any chat longer than 10 turns
Before closing, write or update `docs/HANDOFF-<YYYY-MM-DD>.md`:

```
## Status
[Done / In progress / Blocked]

## What was done
- [function/route changed] — [why]

## Current state
[Does it work? What's confirmed broken? What's unknown?]

## Exact next step
[Single action: "Fix the FileNotFoundError in deploy_nodered() around line 4200"]

## Files touched
- app.py (lines ~XXXX–YYYY)
- nodered/deploy.sh
```

## The HANDOFF is your memory — treat it like source code
It lives in `docs/` and gets committed. Future-you (and the agent) will thank present-you.

## If a bug takes >2 chats to resolve
Add a `## Known context` section to the HANDOFF with:
- What you've already ruled out
- Exact error messages / log lines
- Which approaches failed and why

This prevents the agent from re-exploring dead ends at your expense.
